<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued August 28 at 4:59PM CDT until August 28 at 5:15PM CDT by NWS Saint Louis</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 515 PM CDT
FOR NORTHERN MACOUPIN COUNTY...
At 459 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Carlinville,
moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Palmyra, Nilwood, Modesto, Hettick, Standard City and Scottville.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
